nd of threat seems to be becoming more and more common where parents are unhappy with professionals - in education or social work. Parents need to be aware that this kind of threat will not, under any circumstances, stop interventions - and social workers and teachers must be fully supported in the event of such allegations. Sorry - off topic I know - but home education seems to be the least important factor in this case. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="729" language="en" documentId="1053" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="shazthewombat" date="28 July 2010 9:33pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6869550" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="30" thumbsDown="0" origId="1053" notes="" title="Home education: precious, not dangerous"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="151"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="152" end="729"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>